<HL>
   Calgon Carbon to Buy Assets
</HL>
<DATE>
08/31/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C4
</SO>
<CO>
   CRBN
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   PITTSBURGH -- Calgon Carbon Corp., which produces
activated carbon and supplies related equipment and services,
said it agreed to purchase the operating assets of TMPC Inc.,
Vero Beach, Fla., principally a design and construction
company specializing in solvent recovery, pollution control
and the design of chemical processes. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   Calgon said that sales of the unit last year were about
$10 million, and that it expects to complete the purchase by
mid-September.
